,,7432771434256506880,https://www.linkedin.com/posts/jatin-batra-1a300835_artificialintelligence-generativeai-llm-activity-7432771434256506880-cDXA,jatin-batra-1a300835,["#ArtificialIntelligence","#GenerativeAI","#LLM","#AIInfrastructure","#AIGovernance","#AIEthics","#FutureOfAI"],,https://www.linkedin.com/posts/jatin-batra-1a300835_artificialintelligence-generativeai-llm-activity-7432771434256506880-cDXA,31,Anthropic recently disclosed that three AI labs allegedly ran large-scale distillation attacks on Claude — using ~24,000 fraudulent accounts to generate over 16 million interactions aimed at replicating model capabilities. Distillation itself isn’t new. It’s a legitimate technique to compress or transfer knowledge between models. The controversy begins when it becomes a shortcut to copy capabilities instead of building them. A few reflections: • The real AI battleground may shift from training models to protecting model behavior • “Model moats” look thinner — APIs can become the new extraction surface • Expect tighter access controls, stricter verification, and more aggressive usage monitoring across providers • Developers should treat LLM access like critical infrastructure — have fallback providers and contingency plans The next phase of AI competition may not be about who trains the biggest model — but who can secure, govern, and operationalize intelligence most effectively. #ArtificialIntelligence #GenerativeAI #LLM #AIInfrastructure #AIGovernance #AIEthics #FutureOfAI,2026-02-26T13:00:04.142Z,1,["https://www.linkedin.com/company/anthropicresearch?trk=public_post-text","https://www.linkedin.com/company/bloomberg?trk=public_post-text","https://lnkd.in/dS7jMBJ3","https://hk.linkedin.com/in/naman-tandon-83b6566a?trk=public_post-text","https://sg.linkedin.com/in/haslinda-amin-0a29892b?trk=public_post-text","https://ie.linkedin.com/company/zero-day-con?trk=public_post-text","https://ie.linkedin.com/in/ronanmurphy1?trk=public_post-text","https://www.linkedin.com/company/forcepoint?trk=public_post-text","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/zdc26","http://www.zerodaycon.com/","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/zerodaycon","https://lnkd.in/dWCiFZ75","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/academicpublishing","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/researchintegrity","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/peerreview","https://cygeniq.ai/","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/cygeniq","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/datapoisoning","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/aiintegrity","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/aigovernance","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/enterpriserisk","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/protectai","https://uk.linkedin.com/company/controlai?trk=public_post-text","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/artificialintelligence","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/generativeai","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/llm","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/aiinfrastructure","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/aigovernance","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/aiethics","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/futureofai"]
["https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4D22AQGAUu42NDlPUg/feedshare-shrink_20/B4DZwzpuntHEAM-/0/1770393103063?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=M5tWGDPwTbtpDj1wd5EdV6WcwUumWS3al0D2EUQfc3g"],,7425566879257182208,https://www.linkedin.com/posts/erick-shapumba-303601256_this-trend-is-exposing-the-reality-of-our-activity-7425566879257182208-SUu3,erick-shapumba-303601256,,,https://www.linkedin.com/posts/erick-shapumba-303601256_this-trend-is-exposing-the-reality-of-our-activity-7425566879257182208-SUu3,4,This trend is exposing the reality of our security culture, people are blindly feeding AI their faces, surroundings, habits, and pieces of their personal lives, with zero understanding of where that data goes, how long it’s stored, or who can access it. It’s exhausting trying to teach people how to safeguard their information while they chase trends, not realizing they’re handing over personal data to systems they don’t understand, with no knowledge of how it will be used. The danger isn’t AI, it’s human behavior. The weakest link in the digital world has always been ourselves.,2026-02-06T15:51:44.376Z,0,["https://www.linkedin.com/company/anthropicresearch?trk=public_post-text","https://www.linkedin.com/company/bloomberg?trk=public_post-text","https://lnkd.in/dS7jMBJ3","https://hk.linkedin.com/in/naman-tandon-83b6566a?trk=public_post-text","https://sg.linkedin.com/in/haslinda-amin-0a29892b?trk=public_post-text","https://ie.linkedin.com/company/zero-day-con?trk=public_post-text","https://ie.linkedin.com/in/ronanmurphy1?trk=public_post-text","https://www.linkedin.com/company/forcepoint?trk=public_post-text","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/zdc26","http://www.zerodaycon.com/","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/zerodaycon","https://lnkd.in/dWCiFZ75","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/academicpublishing","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/researchintegrity","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/peerreview","https://cygeniq.ai/","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/cy