w.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/riveapp","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/datavisualization","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/learninginpublic","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/jvm","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/coding","https://lnkd.in/g5NPk44D","https://lnkd.in/gnfXJ-yu","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/python","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/pygame","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/gamedevelopment","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/algorithms","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/astar","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/softwaredevelopment","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/coding","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/projects","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/csuf","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/algorithmengineering","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/spring2026","https://lnkd.in/eHjymfzg","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/codex","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/claudecode","https://lnkd.in/euWRjrUa"]
,,7432507777647837184,https://www.linkedin.com/posts/kshitijaucharmal21_conceptforge-gamedev-graphicsprogramming-activity-7432507777647837184-EXLo,kshitijaucharmal21,["#ConceptForge","#GameDev","#GraphicsProgramming","#Python","#C","#GameEngine","#IndieDev","#AI"],,https://www.linkedin.com/posts/kshitijaucharmal21_conceptforge-gamedev-graphicsprogramming-activity-7432507777647837184-EXLo,28,Big step forward for ConceptForge! After hitting a wall with nanobind (it simply doesn’t support embedding Python into C++ the way I needed), I made the switch to pybind11. And it works beautifully. Just wired up a quick add_cube() binding for testing, and here’s the result: a smooth cube spawning and rotating right inside the engine. Nothing fancy yet… but it’s the foundation for something much bigger. Being able to embed full Python scripting directly into the C++ core opens up insane possibilities: - Rapid prototyping of gameplay mechanics - AI-driven tools & behaviors - Hot-reloading logic without recompiling - And eventually letting creators script their own games in Python while the heavy graphics & performance stay in C++ This is exactly the kind of hybrid power I’ve been chasing. ConceptForge is starting to feel real now. Can’t wait to push this further — next up: exposing more engine systems to Python and building actual logic with it. What do you think — would you rather script your game engine in Python or stick to pure C++? Drop your thoughts below 👇 #ConceptForge #GameDev #GraphicsProgramming #Python #C ++ #GameEngine #IndieDev #AI,2026-02-25T19:32:23.508Z,2,["https://x.com/ma_at_anubis","https://lnkd.in/eZFxzqWa","https://lnkd.in/eYSNmcw9","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/gamedev","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/graphicsprogramming","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/indiedev","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/cpp","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/opengl","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/conceptforge","http://menu.py/","http://impor