,,7424361030765563904,https://www.linkedin.com/posts/alejandro-seijas-nadales-901606212_3d-technicalart-maya-activity-7424361030765563904-jD1G,alejandro-seijas-nadales-901606212,["#3d","#TechnicalArt","#Maya","#Python","#MayaPython","#Scripting","#ToolDevelopment","#3DTools","#Pipeline","#TechnicalArtist","#Rigging","#Animation","#VFX","#3DArt","#PluginsMaya","#DigitalArt","#Workflow","#StudioTools","#QTDesginer"],,https://www.linkedin.com/posts/alejandro-seijas-nadales-901606212_3d-technicalart-maya-activity-7424361030765563904-jD1G,214,Hi Guys!!! 😄 I spent the las few weeks experimenting with mathematical and matrix operations inside Maya and put together a small tool that simulates a force field. The script: • Generates a spherical force field, and • Instantiates multiple meshes across a chosen geometry, placing each instance at the geometry’s vertex world positions. Under the hood I leaned on Maya nodes for distance/vector math; the calculations use the field’s world position, its radius, and each mesh’s world-space center. The meshes themselves can be any shapes the user prefers, so it’s pretty flexible. At the same time, each generated mesh has its own controls, so you can animate each one individually by hand. Or, using the UI you can choose a start and end frame and the values to animate the rotation and/or scale for each instance. I’d appreciate any feedback or ideas for new features. Happy to share this short demo! #3d #TechnicalArt #Maya #Python #MayaPython #Scripting #ToolDevelopment #3DTools #Pipeline #TechnicalArtist #Rigging #Animation #VFX #3DArt #PluginsMaya #DigitalArt #Workflow #StudioTools #QTDesginer,2026-02-03T08:00:07.692Z,6,["https://x.com/ma_at_anubis","https://lnkd.in/eZFxzqWa","https://lnkd.in/eYSNmcw9","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/gamedev","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/graphicsprogramming","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/indiedev","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/cpp","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/opengl","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/conceptforge","http://menu.py/","http://importlib.reload/?trk=public_post-text","http://nuke.menu/","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/vfxstudio","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/animationstudioes","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/python","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/nuke","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/vfx","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/netflix","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/warnerbros","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/conceptforge","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/gamedev","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/graphicsprogramming","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/python","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/c","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/gameengine","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/indiedev","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/ai","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/3d","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/technicalart","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/maya","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/python","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/mayapython","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/scripting","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/tooldevelopment","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/3dtools","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/pipeline","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/technicalartist","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/rigging","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/animation","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/vfx","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/3dart","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/pluginsmaya","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/digitalart","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/workflow","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/studiotools","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/qtdesginer","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/houdini","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/sidefx","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/technicalart","https://www.linkedin.com/fe