["https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D5622AQHYu1ULsIJffQ/feedshare-shrink_800/B56ZwtMP4tKAAg-/0/1770284711801?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=aSo8mPDz3dynnbmQHPvPlhrhOwcrdZiMWWxUzhYn0UY"],,7425112255140089856,https://www.linkedin.com/posts/alexanderrichtertd_which-vfx-software-actually-has-the-best-activity-7425112255140089856-G6PX,alexanderrichtertd,,,https://www.linkedin.com/posts/alexanderrichtertd_which-vfx-software-actually-has-the-best-activity-7425112255140089856-G6PX,56,Which VFX software actually has the best Python API? On this stream, we’re doing a side-by-side code comparison of Maya, 3ds Max, Blender, Houdini and Nuke. We’ll test them on essential TD tasks like creating nodes, setting attributes and navigating documentation to see which API is truly "Pythonic" and which feels stuck in the past. (3ds Max won't win I can tell you that much. ;) ) Finally, we’ll rate each software from 1 to 5 stars and discuss the future of unifying Python standards across the VFX industry. Join our live stream today: https://lnkd.in/g5NPk44D PS. We updated the event from pure Python Blender to include all the DCCs in VFX.,2026-02-05T09:45:13.540Z,12,["https://x.com/ma_at_anubis","https://lnkd.in/eZFxzqWa","https://lnkd.in/eYSNmcw9","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/gamedev","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/graphicsprogramming","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/indiedev","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/cpp","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/opengl","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/conceptforge","http://menu.py/","http://importlib.reload/?trk=public_post-text","http://nuke.menu/","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/vfxstudio","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/animationstudioes","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/python","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/nuke","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/vfx","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/netflix","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/warnerbros","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/ha