,,7434123047760171010,https://www.linkedin.com/posts/santhosh-kumar-4b3349308_python-pygame-gamedevelopment-activity-7434123047760171010-MExH,santhosh-kumar-4b3349308,["#Python","#Pygame","#GameDevelopment","#Algorithms","#AStar","#SoftwareDevelopment","#Coding","#Projects"],,https://www.linkedin.com/posts/santhosh-kumar-4b3349308_python-pygame-gamedevelopment-activity-7434123047760171010-MExH,26,🚀 Excited to share my project – Smart Escape Arena 🎮 I developed this game using Python and Pygame, combining gameplay design with core computer science concepts and advanced algorithms. 🎥 Here’s a short demo of the gameplay! 💡 Concepts & Algorithms Used: • Game Loop Algorithm – Continuous rendering, input handling, and updates • Event Handling – Real-time keyboard input processing • Collision Detection – Rectangle-based collision logic • A (A-Star) Pathfinding Algorithm* – Used for intelligent movement and optimal path selection • State Management – Handling levels, win/lose conditions, and transitions • 2D Rendering Pipeline – Managing sprites, animations, and screen updates 🧠 Core CS Concepts: • Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) • Data Structures (grids, lists for map representation) • Real-time system design 🛠️ Tech Stack: Python, Pygame 🔗 GitHub Repository: https://lnkd.in/gnfXJ-yu This project enhanced my understanding of algorithms like A*, real-time processing, and game logic design. Currently working on deploying it online for public access 🚀 Would love to hear your feedback! #Python #Pygame #GameDevelopment #Algorithms #AStar #SoftwareDevelopment #Coding #Projects,2026-03-02T06:30:53.913Z,0,["https://x.com/ma_at_anubis","https://lnkd.in/eZFxzqWa","https://lnkd.in/eYSNmcw9","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/gamedev","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/graphicsprogramming","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/indiedev","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/cpp","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/opengl","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/conceptfo