kedin.com/feed/hashtag/technicalart","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/vfx","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/claudeai","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/mcp","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/pipeline","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/vex","https://www.linkedin.com/company/rive-app?trk=public_post-text","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/scala","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/functionalprogramming","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/softwareengineering","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/riveapp","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/datavisualization","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/learninginpublic","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/jvm","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/coding","https://lnkd.in/g5NPk44D","https://lnkd.in/gnfXJ-yu","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/python","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/pygame","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/gamedevelopment","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/algorithms","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/astar","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/softwaredevelopment","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/coding","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/projects","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/csuf","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/algorithmengineering","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/spring2026","https://lnkd.in/eHjymfzg","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/codex","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/claudecode","https://lnkd.in/euWRjrUa"]
,,7425178165112721408,https://www.linkedin.com/posts/cgriv_github-crussella0129animus-a-repository-activity-7425178165112721408-5BOp,cgriv,["#Codex","#ClaudeCode"],,https://www.linkedin.com/posts/cgriv_github-crussella0129animus-a-repository-activity-7425178165112721408-5BOp,0,In building Animus ( https://lnkd.in/eHjymfzg ) I discovered something (that might have been common sense to some people). I set out to create a locally running, agentic CLI Tool, much like #Codex or #ClaudeCode , and I succeeded! … the only problem is the “fully local” part still doesn’t work (for the vast majority of people) and that’s due to the physical constraints of computation itself. To run a model that can do any kind of coherent actions at all within the terminal, you need around a 30b model with proper quantization. Unfortunately, at this level, it’s still not a reliably usable tool. This is around what most upper level consumer and gaming hardware can do. Around 70b to 100b is when multi step coding and file calling functions *start* to become possible. This is like enthusiast gaming/light engineering workstation hardware. Only at around 200b (and with a lot of RAM), or a model only accessible on heavy engineering workstation/ Data Center grade computation power, do you get something that will execute complex commands, have a large enough context window to be able to consider “compressed history” files, and actually feel like it’s doing what you say. And even then, API access to Opus 4.5 or Codex 5.2 wins, both in performance and amortized cost over the life of the computer. And that’s why Animus ended up with an API harness 😂,2026-02-05T14:07:07.702Z,0,["https://x.com/ma_at_anubis","https://lnkd.in/eZFxzqWa","https://lnkd.in/eYSNmcw9","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/gamedev","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/graphicsprogramming","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/indiedev","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/cpp","https://www.linkedin.com/feed/hashtag/opengl","h